    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="154"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 9, 1948—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1577. Following is summary Secy’s conversation with T. F. Tsiang rptd accordance
                    his instructions as partial reply urtel 2116 Nov 6 and you may refer to Secy’s
                    comments therein in your conversation with FonMin:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of telegram No. <hi rend="smallcaps">Martel</hi> 111, November
                    6, printed on <ref target="#pg_193">page 193</ref>.]</p>
                <p>Point (1) raised by T. F. Tsiang is considered to be adequately covered by Secy’s
                    personal tel to you Deptel 1490 Oct 26.<note n="49" xml:id="d154fn49">
                        <ref target="frus1948v07#pg_512">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">vii</hi>, p.
                            512</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Secy authorizes following message as further reply urtel 2116:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text quoted in telegram No. <hi rend="smallcaps">Martel</hi> 115,
                    November 8, 9 p.m., printed on <ref target="#pg_195">page 195</ref>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
